        <param>
          <type>uint32_t</type>
          <declname>point</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Retrieves the State of the point specified. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>@SINCE_1_9.25 <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">point</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The point required </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The state of the point specified </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>If point is greater than <ref refid="classDali_1_1HoverEvent_1a1b38e649480daa92ff76e6f3ccfd3efd" kindref="member">GetPointCount()</ref> then this method will return <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1PointState_1a6a1bea9b393f61a1f5f54690c99918f7ac85fd46f126142d63d76b89e575e633e" kindref="member">PointState::FINISHED</ref>. If you set <ref refid="structDali_1_1Actor_1_1Property_1aa00cf4d2c81c442d5bf5c544f96410c3a4bb851eeb9fa52a16ab72e588ccec3ee" kindref="member">Actor::Property::LEAVE_REQUIRED</ref> to true, when the hover event enters the actor, it will receive STARTED state. an actor that received a hover <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1PointState_1a6a1bea9b393f61a1f5f54690c99918f7a83c1abd464d39abcf203a1d8d82ab561" kindref="member">PointState::MOTION</ref> event will receive <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1PointState_1a6a1bea9b393f61a1f5f54690c99918f7a69318fc1aa5eb3b0e7c8270ccf2cccc9" kindref="member">PointState::INTERRUPTED</ref> event when <ref refid="structDali_1_1Actor_1_1Property_1aa00cf4d2c81c442d5bf5c544f96410c3adabd32d5f99491cac08f24d5d6ea86ea" kindref="member">Actor::Property::SENSITIVE</ref> is changed to false. However, an actor that received a hover <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1PointState_1a6a1bea9b393f61a1f5f54690c99918f7a707449cd8718935d89b36e5e1c87fa18" kindref="member">PointState::STARTED</ref> event will not receive any event when <ref refid="structDali_1_1Actor_1_1Property_1aa00cf4d2c81c442d5bf5c544f96410c3adabd32d5f99491cac08f24d5d6ea86ea" kindref="member">Actor::Property::SENSITIVE</ref> is changed to false. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>State </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
